Absa’s Unit Will Lend $50 Million to Farmers in Tanzania, Guardian Reports

-- B y   D a v i d   M a l i n g h a   D o y a
-- 
2011-06-20T08:51:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-20/absa-s-unit-will-lend-50-million-to-farmers-in-tanzania-guardian-reports.html
Absa Group Ltd. (ASA) ’s Tanzanian unit
will extend $50 million of credit to farmers in the East African
nation, the  Guardian reported .  The funds will go to small-scale farmers, food processors
and exporters and importers of agricultural equipment, the Dar
es Salaam-based newspaper said, citing Shafii Mndema, an
agribusiness official at National Bank of Commerce Ltd.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Malingha Doya in  Dar es Salaam  via Nairobi at 
440 or  pmrichardson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Paul Richardson  at   pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  